==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gesticulate
<hw>Ges*tic"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Gesticulated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gesticulating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>gesticulatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>gesticulari</ets> to gesticulate,
fr. <ets>gesticulus</ets> a mimic gesture, gesticulation, dim. of
<ets>gestus</ets> gesture, fr. <ets>gerere</ets>, <ets>gestum</ets>, to
bear, carry, peform. See <er>Gestic</er>.]</ety> <def>To make gestures
or motions, as in speaking; to use postures.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gesticulate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gesticulate
<hw>Ges*tic"u*late</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To represent by gesture;
to act.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

